EN: He committed a serious crime.
ZH: 她对这个罪行感到非常内疚。
EN: She feels very guilty about this crime.
ZH: 在这个社会中犯罪是不被允许的。
EN: Committing crimes is not tolerated in this society.
ZH: 这是一种不可饶恕的罪行。
EN: This is an unforgivable crime.
ZH: 罪犯必须接受法律的制裁。
EN: Criminals must face legal consequences.
ZH: 别忘了，罪有应得。
EN: Don't forget, one reaps what one sows.
ZH: 犯罪者将受到严厉的惩罚。
EN: Criminals will receive severe punishment.
ZH: 不要轻易犯下不可挽回的罪过。
EN: Don't easily commit irredeemable sins.
ZH: 遭受无辜的人受到了严重的罪责。
EN: Innocent people have suffered serious consequences.
ZH: 我们必须对犯罪行为说不。
EN: We must say no to criminal behavior.
ZH: 禁止在此场所犯罪。
EN: Crime is prohibited in this location.
ZH: 他因为一时的愚蠢犯下了罪。
EN: He committed the crime because of a moment of foolishness.
ZH: 许多人在这种情况下都会做出罪行。
EN: Many people would commit crimes in such circumstances.
ZH: 没有人可以逃避罪行。
EN: No one can escape their sins.
ZH: 犯罪不会带来好运。
EN: Crime does not bring good fortune.
ZH: 法律应该对罪行加以制裁。
EN: The law should punish crimes.
ZH: 父母教育应该帮助孩子远离犯罪。
EN: Parents' education should help children stay away from crime.
